iTPMS
Author: Keith Conger <keith.conger@gmail.com>
http://itpms.thecongers.org
License: GPLv2

Motorcycle iTPMS Client Software

Requires:
* An iTPMSystem (http://www.atbs.com.tw/product_TPMS_Module_E.htm)

Current Features:
* Sensor discovery
* Displays tire pressure, temperature and voltage
* User configurable units for pressure and temperature
* User configurable notifications for low/high tire pressure (Sound, vibrate and LED)
* Optional data logging in csv format to /sdcard/itpms

Howto Use:
1) Power on the iTPMSystem
2) Pair your device to the iTPMSystem unit, test with the Vendor supplied app and close it.
3) Launch iTPMSystem, you should see message that you are connected.
   You now need to wait for the sensors to start sending data through the iTPMSystem.
4) Once discovered map them to their wheel locations in the preferences.
5) Enjoy

Software Used:
Android SQLiteAssetHelper
https://github.com/jgilfelt/android-sqlite-asset-helper

AndroidSVG
https://bitbucket.org/paullebeau/androidsvg
